place_description: A really cool coffee shop in old town Cornelius with a cozy local vibe. We serve locally roasted craft coffee and exotic loose leaf teas along with Breakfast and lunch fare made in house, and amazing scrumptious baked goods.

reviews_data.review_text:
Finally made it to WillowWood Coffee in Cornelius. I met Rich, one of the owners. Awesome guy! This is the cutest coffee shop & a great place to get some work done 

Their coffee consists of
3 different beans and is roasted 3 different ways. I took home the Lake Norman blend.

Enjoy!

Josephine
One of the best coffee shops all around. Not only do they have amazing coffee, but they also have delicious food. The inside is adorable and the staff is very welcoming.

I just love this place!  I come here a few times a week to get coffee. The staff is always so warm, welcoming and kind. The coffee is always fresh, and the prices are super reasonable and affordable. Today I got food for the first time, and it did not disappoint. I tried the Hank breakfast sandwich. Not only was it delicious, but it was under $5.  If you haven't yet been to Wild Willow, you have to come check them out! :)
Coffee and food are always great and consistently solid service with a smile.
Coffee was good, atmosphere is great! Very cute little shop, comfy seating, staff was very polite as well.
Friendly staff, good coffee, decent selection of food. It isn't an amazing vibe and the outdoor space is pretty basic but not bad for a quick in/out coffee run.

Great little coffee shop! It needs a bigger sign outside, I almost missed it. I had the cortado and it found it satisfactory. I did which they had a rosseta or something as it was lacking in the art department. Avocado toast was ok. Do prefer whole avocado as opposed to guacamole. The breakfast bowl has avocado slices. Smoothie pretty good, not too sweet. You could really taste the fruit and it did not seem like they added any sugar.

This is a cute coffee spot with great options. I had an oatmeal cookie latte ( half sweet) and it was delicious. My family and I stopped here on Fathers Day weekend and all 10 of us was very happy with our coffee choices. Note: check out their current drink specials in the wall instead of their menu.
Super cute small coffee shop. Everyone is always very nice.
Iced mocha was probably the best I've ever had. Not too busy so I hope it gets more business, super cute place!

Great coffee, (especially the Ethiopian) great food and friendly baristas.  It's right on our corner so I go all the time.  Has a patio to sit outside when it's nice.  A super addition to the neighborhood.
Great little coffee shop-  we enjoyed the outdoor seating. They were out of cold brew but the iced americano they suggested was awesome!
Baked oatmeal was excellent. And custom made me a dark  mocha with blackberry.

Great Cortado. Good looking pastries.
Will definitely be back when on that side of the lake
I had a cortado, i believe the roaster over toasted the coffee beans because it tasted overly bitter and burnt.
Nice place , very nice service
Love this cafe! Great options and variety, homey atmosphere, friendly staff.
Great coffee shop with awesome baked goods
The new Avacado toast with pickled egg was surprisingly delicious!  Loved it!  I also had the white chocolate, raspberry latte which was very good and not too sweet.

We had ourselves a honey/rose latte and a raspberry white chocolate latte. Both were super light, refreshing and not too sweet. You can tell they use quality honey. Also tried birch beer for the first time. It's like the best root beer you'll ever have. Definitely come here for the coffee and stay for the adorable atmosphere.
One of best coffe in the area! Thank you. Wish you work till 3 pm though))
Nice little coffee shop. Service was excellent. WiFi worked. Cappuccino was excellent.

My favorite coffee shop in the Lake Norman area. Love their lattes (The Bluestone and Oh Wow! are my favorites). Prices are more economical than some other cafes in the area, which makes me come here more than the others (I'm tired of paying $7-8 for a latte at other cafes.) They also have good bfast and lunch options. My only critique is the lack of gluten-free bread, which is a pretty easy option for cafes to have these days (GF bread can be kept in a freezer or fridge for a long time without going bad.) I love the nice atmosphere with a chill, peaceful vibe. Great place to get some writing done. Thank you!
The Whitewater signature latte is divine, the staff is super friendly and helpful, food is fresh and delicious, you can't go wrong here!

Very cute coffee shop!! Went there for the first time and the staff was very helpful and told me what their most popular drinks and food are. It is small but very cozy and a nice place to sit down and get some work done.
Love the coffee and atmosphere!

Really excellent little shop. The staff are wonderfully nice and the atmosphere is really lovely. The food they have on menu is good and well made however the only criticism I have is that the menu is not very inclusive of dietary issues. They had some vegetarian options but no true dairy free/vegan options. I would give this place a full 5 stars if they added some dairy free or vegan pastries and menu items. Would make this place AWESOME!
The perfect spot for a cup of your favorite brew. BUT if you just sit and talk or do your work without ordering more than coffee, TIP as much as you can. After all,  you did get a nice sit down.
This place is so cute! One of my favorite coffee shops I've ever been too. I got a hot vanilla latte and everything bagel.
Your pastries are my obsession.  I need to stop visiting but don't worry --- I'm addicted and I'll be back soon.    so incredible!
Great coffee and breakfast sandwich with reasonable prices! Def recommend
Awesome coffee shop! Barnstable are friendly and decor is on point!

Very friendly and customer service oriented.  They have a full menu of food and coffee options.  This is a great space to grab a drink and read, work, or meet with others.  Their wifi works great for Zoom meetings, too.

Nice new Coffee Shop. I got he "Oh Wow" which was Peanut butter, White Chocolate, Espresso, and Steamed Milk. It was really good. I personally like a good strong Peanut butter flavor and this was perfect . My Wife got the "Whitewater" which was Blackberry and White Chocolate and she said it was really good as well! We will definitely come again.

Been here a few times and it's been pretty good.... Last time in person that waiting on me it was not very nice at all.
When they have people waiting in line, there's never enough help .....

The place was cute and the service was quick. 3 stars because the vanilla Chai latte was discusting. I'm an avid Chai drinker and this was horrible. I took the $6 loss and dumped it out after the first sip. Bummer
Awesome local community coffee shop. Mario is the best!!
The staff is lovely and the bites I have had were decent a little overpriced. I love love love the coffee!!

Lovely coffee house, delicious coffee and sandwiches. I'm giving 3 stars because this is the 3rd time I came here to to have  breakfast and coffee with a friend and had to take it to go because there was no place to eat. People with laptops taking up practically every table, one person with a laptop taking up one whole table. Owner needs to add more tables or somehow manage the existing ones so that people not drinking coffee can't stop people who are actually there for a social reason have a place to drink theirs!
What a wonderful start to my 1st day in NC- moved across the country! Had the prosciutto Benedict and a latte....in such a beautiful environment!

Great experience from the customer service to the delicious food. My wife got an oatmeal cookie latte with a scone and I got a smoothie with a ham and Brie panini. Everything was amazing. We will be back!
Friendly, helpful team. Lots of plugs to sit down and do a little work or have a quick meeting.
Cappachino was a little big by my standards, but really exceptional taste, feel, and quality.
A little more business than cozy. Excellent and friendly service.
Willow Wood Coffee has become a great staple in the area. I really love their Mocha and the prosciutto bre fig toast is so good they started making it all day!
Great atmosphere, coffee and food.  The staff is wonderful!  Try the raspberry tea, my favorite!!
Great place and atmosphere only con is the window shades were a little dusty.
Great little coffee shop. Born and raised in Cornelius and a chuld of a small businessowner her, love to visit small businesses and glad to see them flourish.
One of my very favorite coffee shops! I love their iced lattes and pastries - especially the apple cream cheese muffins and the oatmeal cookie latte!

The staff is incredibly friendly, the latte I had was delicious and the whole environment was cozy and comfortable. Will definitely be back! I was having an awful day and both Rich and the blue haired girl (I'm sorry I didn't catch her name) made it much better. Thanks y'all!! Please support local and keep these lovely people around!
Great coffee and wonderful staff in a convenient location!

Pros: Tasty coffee and snacks.
Cons: Nobody cleans the place. Pay attention to cobwebs on light fixtures and old liquids stuck on mugs.

Thrilled to have Willow Wood coffee! It's the best coffee north of Charlotte. The iced coffee and espresso are high quality and the matcha is the best I have had in Charlotte (not overly sweetened). Be sure to try the delicious cafe food, and enjoy the adorable ambiance. The staff are incredibly friendly and helpful too!
Great find! It's a sweet little gem with great coffee/tea, friendly staff, and is appropriately priced. There is nothing chain-like about this place and I am happy to have found it!

Came all the way from the UK and found a new favourite coffee shop!  First thing you get when you walk in is a warm welcome and a nice chilled atmosphere. Sit down and use the complimentary phone charger. (Nice touch) and if you're a gullible English man then your fiancee will point out the jackalope and convince you it's real!  On to the important stuff. My americano is pretty hard to mess up, but damn that was nice coffee!  The other half had the "bluestone " and said it was to die for. Then........THEN.......the muffins!  Omg those muffins! 'Nuff said lol. As you can tell I love this place.  Come give it a try!
Great breakfast sandwiches, cold brew and pastries with a neighborhood vibe. This place puts Starbucks to shame!
Such a comfortable and welcoming coffee shop in Cornelius.  Great drink and food menu. Free wifi, plenty of parking.

You two young ladies provided me with a free coffee on Veterans day. This old Vet just wants to thank you publicly for your kindness as it was very much appreciated.
The coffee was great.....thank you.

Great coffee & food. Very good place to go for small groups; however, there is no large group seating. That has been a problem as we have a large group who want a coffee shop with comfortable seating for 6-7  people.
Great coffee, great staff, and great environment. I highly recommend this place!
They never have brewed coffee, at a coffee shop. It makes no sense.
Nice and comfy. Great atmosphere

2 of the things I wanted to order were out, including drip coffee.  The breakfast sandwich I ordered they forgot to make it.  20 minutes later I went and asked and they said they forgot.  They ended up making it and it was good.
Awesome new coffee spot. Coffee was good. Food also looked good will have to try next time.
The bees knees is delicious

I love this place I actually feel like I'm at a cute coffee shop out of town. I love the vibe and then I found out you are both from West Virginia which I am as well. Go mountaineers and herd. The flavors are great. I want to try them all just a suggestion coffee flight day? I just wish I was part owner so I can enjoy this relaxing earthy vibe on the daily. The baked peach oatmeal is to die for. Thanks willow wood
Good latte & comfy booths!

Amazing Hangout...
Rich and crew totally amazing...
Cute New place with friendly staff.

Back on my ever evolving quest to try all the best coffee in Charlotte Metro  
Many new spots have come on the scene 
Loving this newer spot in Cornelius... Phenomenal experience! Fresh adorable atmosphere. Wonderful service from owner Rich and his baristas.

Indulged in a: Oatmeal Cookie Latte -
Oat milk, brown sugar, vanilla, cinnamon goodness all mellowed into a local roast 

Certainly drop in to WillowWood Coffee when in the area 

As they say, "Coffee is always a good idea" 

Happy Thursday, friends!
Very nice atmosphere.
Busy after 8:30am. Staff was very helpful and food and drinks were delicious.
What a great spot! Have to pay attention or you'll pass it, glad I stopped in today. Good customer service, nice atmosphere. The Lake Norman blend coffee super good. Bought a bag to take home!
My new favorite coffee spot! The Oatmeal Cookie (drink) is the best! Friendly staff and quick service.
I think this is my new neighborhood coffee joint.  Coffee is delicious each time, but then they are not using burnt beans.  Try the Brie and prosciutto breakfast!

Cold drinks served in glasses not plastic cups. Our little dog had a pup cup/bowl, we had them add a little sprinkle of cinnamon, she is spoiled. Dogs are welcome inside and out on the patio. The food is more savory than sweet, which I like. Overall I'm impressed and I will be coming back to try something new.
Nice little place.
Peach baked oatmeal and the eggs Benedict were very good. Drinks made to our tastes and very yummy. Great atmosphere. Employees welcoming and friendly.
Apple fritter. Great coffee and food! I've loved everything I've ordered so far.

My drink was great! I got a sugar free vanilla oat milk latte with chocolate added. The only downfall is that it was just lukewarm

My boyfriend got a cold brew but it tastes slightly burnt
Great spot!

Stopped by this cute spot with my husband today and we both enjoyed the coffee! Service was excellent and loved the relaxing environment. Super happy to have such a nice spot nearby with amazing coffee :)
friendly service and great selection of yummy treats. a welcome addition to our area!
Excellent service. Great new coffee shop. I enjoyed the relaxing and clean environment. Of course the coffee was delicious.

I have been to Willow Wood Coffee a few times since they recently opened for my usual, non-fat latte, either on ice or hot, depending on the weather. Best latte, for my taste with deep, full flavor. Unfortunately, they do not sell their espresso beans.I have only had my lattes to-go but look forward to trying some of their interesting menu items & being able to stay to enjoy the lovely open, airy decor. Very friendly, welcoming staff.
Excellent coffee shop, can't speak for every menu item, but really enjoyed the latte's and smoothies!
Great little spot. Tried a cortado (not on menu) and it was on point!
Great coffee,  friendly environment..

Been here a couple of times since they opened. I'm actually a tea drinker and it is nice to find a local business that offers loose leaf tea. So far, I have had their Morning Fog with oat milk and just a hot Masala Chai.
The service is friendly, the place is very clean and the ambiance is nice. Most tables have charging stations or outlets and the do offer wifi. They also have some outdoor seating for the beautiful weather.
They offer a wide selection of non-dairy milks which I appreciate.
My sister has had their coffee and she is a fan. Not bitter and they make it super hot just how she likes them.
Shopping center has parking though it may get a little tight during busy hours. Highly recommend.
